<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">&#8220;<b>It has already been in touch with a number of potential buyers</b>, according to a person briefed on the matter,â DealBook writes. Onyx, which makes biopharmaceutical drugs, formally rejected Amgenâs approach on Friday afternoon, and the companyâs shares began rising in after-hours trading soon afterward. âA sale of Onyx, based in California, would be the latest deal in the health care industry, one of the busiest for mergers and acquisitions in recent years.â</p>
